Description: A sealing for an unknown object, probably a document, incorporating a few strands of palm-fibre: an oval impression from an intaglio gem with Eros running right. Unfired pale yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3638)
